And so, it's across the board.

00:16:44.590 --> 00:16:45.410 align:middle line:90%
It's a food source.

00:16:45.410 --> 00:16:46.210 align:middle line:90%
What is McDonald's?

00:16:46.210 --> 00:16:49.460 align:middle line:84%
It needs the food source of
all the customers coming in

00:16:49.460 --> 00:16:50.650 align:middle line:90%
and feeding it, right?

00:16:50.650 --> 00:16:53.650 align:middle line:84%
The point is that
there's this feeding

00:16:53.650 --> 00:16:57.370 align:middle line:84%
system of the current
economy that, essentially,

00:16:57.370 --> 00:16:59.770 align:middle line:84%
is looking to get the
lifeblood, the energy of people.

00:16:59.770 --> 00:17:02.410 align:middle line:84%
And it wants and it needs
to maintain that, right?

00:17:02.410 --> 00:17:05.650 align:middle line:84%
McDonald's has to
keep that market.

00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:08.342 align:middle line:84%
What if McDonald's lost a
billion customers next year?

00:17:08.342 --> 00:17:09.550 align:middle line:90%
They would probably collapse.

00:17:09.550 --> 00:17:10.119 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They're at the creek.

00:17:10.119 --> 00:17:10.390 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right?

00:17:10.390 --> 00:17:11.470 align:middle line:90%
They'd probably collapse.

00:17:11.470 --> 00:17:13.579 align:middle line:90%
So there's this feeding process.

00:17:13.579 --> 00:17:17.140 align:middle line:84%
So there's an aspect,
as I said, of a mutual,

00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:19.359 align:middle line:84%
I call it, the puppet
master and the puppet.

00:17:19.359 --> 00:17:20.440 align:middle line:90%
They're entangled.

00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:22.030 align:middle line:84%
The puppet master
doesn't realize.

00:17:22.030 --> 00:17:23.020 align:middle line:90%
He thinks, oh, I'm controlling.

00:17:23.020 --> 00:17:23.500 align:middle line:90%
I'm the elite.

00:17:23.500 --> 00:17:24.579 align:middle line:90%
I'm controlling humanity.

00:17:24.579 --> 00:17:30.410 align:middle line:84%
But no, actually, this is my
food source for my economy.

00:17:30.410 --> 00:17:35.470 align:middle line:84%
And so, I think that there's a
real interesting question here

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:38.560 align:middle line:84%
of when we talk about
depopulation agenda, which

00:17:38.560 --> 00:17:42.300 align:middle line:84%
people, like Gates and others,
are they essentially trying

00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:45.840 align:middle line:84%
to control the
collapse of economies?

00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:47.970 align:middle line:84%
Because companies like
McDonald's and others

00:17:47.970 --> 00:17:49.240 align:middle line:90%
will also suffer.

00:17:49.240 --> 00:17:51.060 align:middle line:90%
So it's very interesting to me.

00:17:51.060 --> 00:17:53.340 align:middle line:84%
I think there is a real
debate within elite.

00:17:53.340 --> 00:17:56.125 align:middle line:84%
I don't think that the elite
are unanimous in, so far,

00:17:56.125 --> 00:17:57.750 align:middle line:84%
as they're saying,
we-- obviously, they

00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:59.640 align:middle line:84%
want their food
source to be humanity.

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:02.790 align:middle line:84%
But if humanity does
depopulate, what does that mean?

00:18:02.790 --> 00:18:05.820 align:middle line:84%
Does that mean that they,
then, lose their economy?

00:18:05.820 --> 00:18:07.170 align:middle line:90%
That they lose their customers?

00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:10.470 align:middle line:84%
Or will they just be left
with a smaller population

00:18:10.470 --> 00:18:12.733 align:middle line:84%
that, essentially,
these major corporations

00:18:12.733 --> 00:18:13.650 align:middle line:90%
will be in control of?

00:18:13.650 --> 00:18:16.500 align:middle line:84%
Because as we saw during the
lockdowns, what happened was,

00:18:16.500 --> 00:18:18.480 align:middle line:84%
many small businesses
were closed down,

00:18:18.480 --> 00:18:20.890 align:middle line:84%
but the big ones continued
to expand, right?

00:18:20.890 --> 00:18:21.690 align:middle line:90%
The Amazons.

00:18:21.690 --> 00:18:24.000 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You're right on
when you talk about control.

00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:25.980 align:middle line:84%
Let's go back to
Neil Kramer again

00:18:25.980 --> 00:18:27.570 align:middle line:90%
and look at what he has to say.

00:18:27.570 --> 00:18:29.850 align:middle line:84%
You two seemed like you might
have talked on the phone

00:18:29.850 --> 00:18:32.250 align:middle line:90%
because you're pretty similar.

00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:36.150 align:middle line:10%
>>KRAMER: I went to my very
first 4th of July barbecue

00:18:36.150 --> 00:18:39.510 align:middle line:10%
this year, and the people I was
with were excellent and lovely,

00:18:39.510 --> 00:18:43.920 align:middle line:10%
and they were patriotic in
an intelligent, and broad,

00:18:43.920 --> 00:18:45.270 align:middle line:10%
and human way.

00:18:45.270 --> 00:18:47.400 align:middle line:84%
And they were like,
we like our community.

00:18:47.400 --> 00:18:48.630 align:middle line:90%
God bless America.

00:18:48.630 --> 00:18:50.400 align:middle line:90%
Let's have some sausages, right?

00:18:50.400 --> 00:18:54.480 align:middle line:84%
During that time, I saw all
these flags out, of course.

00:18:54.480 --> 00:18:56.850 align:middle line:10%
And I know what the
people are thinking, which

00:18:56.850 --> 00:18:58.360 align:middle line:10%
is, we like our way of life.

00:18:58.360 --> 00:19:00.510 align:middle line:84%
We do have certain
freedoms here that appear

00:19:00.510 --> 00:19:02.280 align:middle line:90%
to be disappearing elsewhere.

00:19:02.280 --> 00:19:04.470 align:middle line:90%
We like the way we do things.

00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:07.350 align:middle line:84%
And the principle
of what's happening

00:19:07.350 --> 00:19:10.920 align:middle line:84%
in America in its pure
state is quite good.

00:19:10.920 --> 00:19:12.820 align:middle line:90%
And I would agree with that.

00:19:12.820 --> 00:19:16.050 align:middle line:10%
However, if they knew what
that flag actually represented,

00:19:16.050 --> 00:19:19.410 align:middle line:10%
they would set it on fire
because the flag is not

00:19:19.410 --> 00:19:21.330 align:middle line:10%
what they think
it is, and that's

00:19:21.330 --> 00:19:23.400 align:middle line:10%
the great dilemma that we
talked about last time,

00:19:23.400 --> 00:19:25.260 align:middle line:10%
the invisibility of empire.

00:19:25.260 --> 00:19:30.780 align:middle line:10%
To wave a stars and
stripes or a union flag

00:19:30.780 --> 00:19:36.660 align:middle line:10%
is a very unusual thing to
do because it is emblazoned

00:19:36.660 --> 00:19:40.830 align:middle line:10%
with these symbols
of subjecting oneself

00:19:40.830 --> 00:19:43.080 align:middle line:10%
to control outside control.

00:19:43.080 --> 00:19:46.350 align:middle line:10%
And when you raise that
flag, you're not saying,

00:19:46.350 --> 00:19:49.620 align:middle line:10%
I like my community
and my kindred spirits.

00:19:49.620 --> 00:19:51.332 align:middle line:10%
You are giving your power away.

00:19:51.332 --> 00:19:52.290 align:middle line:10%
>>MEREDITH: Absolutely.

00:19:52.290 --> 00:19:54.840 align:middle line:10%
So sovereignty and
the reformation

00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:57.660 align:middle line:10%
of political systems.

00:19:57.660 --> 00:19:58.500 align:middle line:10%
>>KRAMER: Discuss.

00:19:58.500 --> 00:20:01.890 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, political systems.

00:20:01.890 --> 00:20:06.000 align:middle line:10%
Again, my benchmark is when
I look at the body politic

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:08.220 align:middle line:10%
in England, in the
United Kingdom,

00:20:08.220 --> 00:20:12.010 align:middle line:10%
in Britain, however you
want to describe it,

00:20:12.010 --> 00:20:13.860 align:middle line:10%
I don't see any wisdom.

00:20:13.860 --> 00:20:17.790 align:middle line:10%
There was wisdom in the
'50s and '60s a little bit,

00:20:17.790 --> 00:20:20.040 align:middle line:10%
from what I can
gather from history.

00:20:20.040 --> 00:20:22.230 align:middle line:10%
And my father assures
me that in the '70s,

00:20:22.230 --> 00:20:25.710 align:middle line:10%
there were the last vestiges
of wisdom in politics.

00:20:25.710 --> 00:20:30.090 align:middle line:10%
When I started to open my eyes
as a young man in the '80s,

00:20:30.090 --> 00:20:31.740 align:middle line:10%
I saw no wisdom.

00:20:31.740 --> 00:20:32.700 align:middle line:10%
None at all.

00:20:32.700 --> 00:20:35.040 align:middle line:10%
So I can't understand
how you can

00:20:35.040 --> 00:20:38.220 align:middle line:10%
have a system of people
with no wisdom determining

00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:41.040 align:middle line:10%
the administration of
a country and the laws

00:20:41.040 --> 00:20:44.160 align:middle line:10%
that govern that
behavior in that country.

00:20:44.160 --> 00:20:46.860 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't make any sense to me.

00:20:46.860 --> 00:20:51.580 align:middle line:84%
For that reason, I refuse to
give my consent to that system.

00:20:51.580 --> 00:20:55.320 align:middle line:10%
So I refuse to give it
my philosophical energy,

00:20:55.320 --> 00:20:59.940 align:middle line:10%
and I refuse to give it my
vote because the vote is

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:03.240 align:middle line:10%
the primary way of giving
consent to a system.

00:21:03.240 --> 00:21:04.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Is he right, Sean?

00:21:04.590 --> 00:21:05.520 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Yes.

00:21:05.520 --> 00:21:06.320 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:21:06.320 --> 00:21:07.000 align:middle line:90%
If we're talking about--

00:21:07.000 --> 00:21:08.667 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You hesitated
for a little bit.

00:21:08.667 --> 00:21:13.520 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Well, there are
interesting aspects to this.

00:21:13.520 --> 00:21:16.010 align:middle line:84%
So for me, for example,
in its principle,

00:21:16.010 --> 00:21:17.707 align:middle line:84%
what America
represents-- and this

00:21:17.707 --> 00:21:19.790 align:middle line:84%
is what I think a lot of
people when we're talking

00:21:19.790 --> 00:21:20.990 align:middle line:90%
about patriotism in America.

00:21:20.990 --> 00:21:24.710 align:middle line:84%
It's a little bit different
than some other countries.

00:21:24.710 --> 00:21:26.330 align:middle line:90%
America, in its essence--

00:21:26.330 --> 00:21:28.670 align:middle line:84%
remember, Declaration
and the Constitution--

00:21:28.670 --> 00:21:33.530 align:middle line:84%
is meant to be a revolutionary
country against the empire,

00:21:33.530 --> 00:21:34.520 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:21:34.520 --> 00:21:36.740 align:middle line:84%
And basically asserting,
for the first time

00:21:36.740 --> 00:21:41.990 align:middle line:84%
in the modern world, the innate
human rights of the individual

00:21:41.990 --> 00:21:43.460 align:middle line:84%
that we are endowed
by our creator

00:21:43.460 --> 00:21:45.230 align:middle line:84%
with these rights,
these God-given rights.

00:21:45.230 --> 00:21:46.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: It started
the right way.

00:21:46.760 --> 00:21:47.000 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right.

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:49.333 align:middle line:10%
And so, I think that's what
people still hold on to when

00:21:49.333 --> 00:21:50.660 align:middle line:10%
we're patriotic despite--

00:21:50.660 --> 00:21:52.160 align:middle line:10%
and then what
happened is that there

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:56.540 align:middle line:10%
has been an explosion of
this federal government.

00:21:56.540 --> 00:21:58.790 align:middle line:90%
It's a huge behemoth.

00:21:58.790 --> 00:22:01.730 align:middle line:84%
It's indebted us,
we, the taxpayers,

00:22:01.730 --> 00:22:02.810 align:middle line:90%
for 30 plus trillion.

00:22:02.810 --> 00:22:04.580 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's almost
a joke at this point.

00:22:04.580 --> 00:22:06.830 align:middle line:84%
It's like, we know we're not
going to pay this, right?

00:22:06.830 --> 00:22:09.205 align:middle line:84%
But the point is that this
federal government is massive.

00:22:09.205 --> 00:22:11.107 align:middle line:84%
It began with the
First World War.

00:22:11.107 --> 00:22:13.190 align:middle line:84%
Before the First World
War, the federal government

00:22:13.190 --> 00:22:15.980 align:middle line:90%
was 6% of the American GDP.

00:22:15.980 --> 00:22:18.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean, now, it's grown
to what proportion.

00:22:18.770 --> 00:22:21.470 align:middle line:84%
I can't even imagine because
it's a major contractor for--

00:22:21.470 --> 00:22:23.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, it pays
major contracts

00:22:23.510 --> 00:22:25.610 align:middle line:84%
to the military
industrial complex, to--

00:22:25.610 --> 00:22:29.390 align:middle line:84%
you name it-- big pharma, to
the major medical industrial

00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:32.725 align:middle line:84%
complex, the welfare state, all
these aspects, Social Security.

00:22:32.725 --> 00:22:34.850 align:middle line:84%
All these things are this
is huge amounts of money,

00:22:34.850 --> 00:22:36.680 align:middle line:84%
and infrastructure,
and bureaucracies.

00:22:36.680 --> 00:22:39.050 align:middle line:84%
So you have a massive
federal government

00:22:39.050 --> 00:22:42.170 align:middle line:84%
that wasn't necessarily the
intention in our Constitution.

00:22:42.170 --> 00:22:44.090 align:middle line:84%
So when he talks
about voting, yeah, I

00:22:44.090 --> 00:22:49.100 align:middle line:84%
agree there is a system that
is entrenched and is moving us

00:22:49.100 --> 00:22:52.140 align:middle line:84%
into a direction of globalism,
as I wrote in my New World

00:22:52.140 --> 00:22:52.940 align:middle line:90%
Order book.

00:22:52.940 --> 00:22:54.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
the empire modality,

00:22:54.980 --> 00:22:57.740 align:middle line:84%
which is government at
a global level, which

00:22:57.740 --> 00:23:00.097 align:middle line:84%
takes the power away from
us, the individuals, which

00:23:00.097 --> 00:23:02.180 align:middle line:84%
is what our Constitution
was supposed to be about.

00:23:02.180 --> 00:23:05.950 align:middle line:84%
The rights that we give the
federal government certain role

00:23:05.950 --> 00:23:06.750 align:middle line:90%
to play.

00:23:06.750 --> 00:23:08.420 align:middle line:84%
And then beyond
that, it's supposed

00:23:08.420 --> 00:23:10.610 align:middle line:84%
to be reserved to the States
and the people therein.

00:23:10.610 --> 00:23:13.787 align:middle line:84%
And that's
decentralization, right?

00:23:13.787 --> 00:23:16.370 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're talking about
in this time, decentralization

00:23:16.370 --> 00:23:17.840 align:middle line:84%
of power, bringing
the power back home,

00:23:17.840 --> 00:23:19.215 align:middle line:84%
bringing back to
the communities,

00:23:19.215 --> 00:23:21.050 align:middle line:84%
to the county level,
to the state level.

00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:23.300 align:middle line:84%
That's more manageable
for us as individuals.

00:23:23.300 --> 00:23:27.410 align:middle line:84%
Once it gets to the level of the
UN, and the Hague, and the EU,

00:23:27.410 --> 00:23:31.640 align:middle line:84%
and the various agreements and
accords that are governing us,

00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:33.500 align:middle line:84%
and treaties that
are governing us,

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:36.020 align:middle line:84%
what say do we have anymore
as individuals, right?

00:23:36.020 --> 00:23:40.620 align:middle line:84%
If the Paris Treaty forces us
to take on carbon emissions,

00:23:40.620 --> 00:23:41.420 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:23:41.420 --> 00:23:44.330 align:middle line:84%
As an individual, I have no
say in that anymore, right?

00:23:44.330 --> 00:23:46.760 align:middle line:84%
So that's my point is that
we've taken power so far

00:23:46.760 --> 00:23:47.840 align:middle line:90%
away from the individual.

00:23:47.840 --> 00:23:49.798 align:middle line:84%
That's taken the authority
away, and that's not

00:23:49.798 --> 00:23:51.933 align:middle line:84%
what I believe our American
Constitution was about

00:23:51.933 --> 00:23:53.100 align:middle line:90%
and our founders were about.

00:23:53.100 --> 00:23:54.955 align:middle line:84%
So I do have that
patriotism, and that's

00:23:54.955 --> 00:23:56.330 align:middle line:84%
a different
patriotism in America

00:23:56.330 --> 00:23:58.400 align:middle line:84%
than it is for England,
which is grappling

00:23:58.400 --> 00:24:01.550 align:middle line:84%
with an empire for hundreds
and hundreds of years.

00:24:01.550 --> 00:24:05.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can the individual
control the power himself

00:24:05.600 --> 00:24:07.185 align:middle line:90%
and do a good job?

00:24:07.185 --> 00:24:08.810 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: What do you
mean by the power?

00:24:08.810 --> 00:24:11.655 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: By taking things
into their own hands.

00:24:11.655 --> 00:24:13.280 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Of course,
we do it every day.

00:24:13.280 --> 00:24:15.950 align:middle line:84%
I believe-- see, even with
economics, for example,

00:24:15.950 --> 00:24:17.690 align:middle line:84%
I believe that we
make choices, right?

00:24:17.690 --> 00:24:19.370 align:middle line:84%
We take the power into
our hands when we decide

00:24:19.370 --> 00:24:20.453 align:middle line:90%
what to do with our money.

00:24:20.453 --> 00:24:22.380 align:middle line:84%
If I have my money, I
want to invest in you.

00:24:22.380 --> 00:24:25.550 align:middle line:84%
I want to buy your product,
I'm investing in you, right?

00:24:25.550 --> 00:24:26.690 align:middle line:90%
If I buy someone's product.

00:24:26.690 --> 00:24:29.210 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Then, again, you could
make the wrong decision, right?

00:24:29.210 --> 00:24:30.030 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: But what's wrong?

00:24:30.030 --> 00:24:31.405 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the point
of the question

00:24:31.405 --> 00:24:33.860 align:middle line:84%
is, of course, there's
a right and wrong.

00:24:33.860 --> 00:24:35.490 align:middle line:84%
You can look at the
global perspective.

00:24:35.490 --> 00:24:37.448 align:middle line:84%
You could say, there's
ecological consequences.

00:24:37.448 --> 00:24:40.460 align:middle line:84%
You could look at the
consequences for our health.

00:24:40.460 --> 00:24:42.440 align:middle line:84%
If I eat McDonald's, it's
probably not the best

00:24:42.440 --> 00:24:43.550 align:middle line:90%
for my health, right?

00:24:43.550 --> 00:24:45.948 align:middle line:84%
We do have, of course,
the opportunity,

00:24:45.948 --> 00:24:47.240 align:middle line:90%
but that's what freedom allows.

00:24:47.240 --> 00:24:49.700 align:middle line:84%
Freedom has to give us
the right to be wrong.

00:24:49.700 --> 00:24:53.080 align:middle line:84%
If we take away freedom,
then, of course,

00:24:53.080 --> 00:24:54.830 align:middle line:84%
who's going to say
what's right and wrong?

00:24:54.830 --> 00:24:55.340 align:middle line:90%
The state?

00:24:55.340 --> 00:24:56.900 align:middle line:84%
Am I going to trust
the state to tell me

00:24:56.900 --> 00:24:58.430 align:middle line:84%
this is what you going
to do for your body?

00:24:58.430 --> 00:24:59.990 align:middle line:90%
You must take these medications.

00:24:59.990 --> 00:25:00.980 align:middle line:90%
You must eat this food.

00:25:00.980 --> 00:25:02.230 align:middle line:90%
You must listen to this music.

00:25:02.230 --> 00:25:04.425 align:middle line:84%
You must listen to this
narrative and the news.

00:25:04.425 --> 00:25:05.300 align:middle line:90%
You must do this job.

00:25:05.300 --> 00:25:06.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Do this, do that.

00:25:06.750 --> 00:25:10.100 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I mean, no, that's
never going to work in humans.

00:25:10.100 --> 00:25:12.180 align:middle line:84%
Humans are innate
desires for freedom.

00:25:12.180 --> 00:25:14.360 align:middle line:84%
That's why every
empire falls because it

00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:17.085 align:middle line:84%
can't withstand the pressure
of the human saying I'm

00:25:17.085 --> 00:25:17.885 align:middle line:90%
a free being.

00:25:17.885 --> 00:25:19.710 align:middle line:90%
You can't tell me what to do.

00:25:19.710 --> 00:25:22.400 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You can't
control them all the time.

00:25:22.400 --> 00:25:25.850 align:middle line:84%
What is transhumanism
mean to you?

00:25:25.850 --> 00:25:29.247 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: So transhumanism
is a fascinating subject.

00:25:29.247 --> 00:25:31.580 align:middle line:84%
And again, we get into it a
little bit in the "Best Kept

00:25:31.580 --> 00:25:34.450 align:middle line:90%
Secret" docuseries.

00:25:34.450 --> 00:25:40.700 align:middle line:84%
To me, it's basically a desire
to remake the human being.

00:25:40.700 --> 00:25:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And there's different
facets to it.

00:25:42.340 --> 00:25:45.910 align:middle line:84%
There is genetic
modification, at gene editing,

00:25:45.910 --> 00:25:47.590 align:middle line:84%
things like this
using mRNA technology.

00:25:47.590 --> 00:25:49.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: There's a
physical alteration--

00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:50.683 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: There's physical.

00:25:50.683 --> 00:25:53.590 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: --and a mental change?

00:25:53.590 --> 00:25:55.780 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Well, I
mean, for example,

00:25:55.780 --> 00:25:59.410 align:middle line:84%
you take Elon Musk's Neuralink,
right, which is essentially

00:25:59.410 --> 00:26:03.382 align:middle line:84%
connecting our brains to
be wireless in interfacing

00:26:03.382 --> 00:26:05.590 align:middle line:84%
with something, wirelessly,
with a computer wireless.

00:26:05.590 --> 00:26:07.120 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Hook us up
with wireless computers

00:26:07.120 --> 00:26:07.730 align:middle line:90%
and satellites.

00:26:07.730 --> 00:26:07.750 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Right.

00:26:07.750 --> 00:26:08.860 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:26:08.860 --> 00:26:10.700 align:middle line:90%
So there's many facets to it.

00:26:10.700 --> 00:26:12.460 align:middle line:84%
But the idea, ultimately,
is redesigning

00:26:12.460 --> 00:26:16.690 align:middle line:84%
the human, saying that humanity
has not reached its peak

00:26:16.690 --> 00:26:18.610 align:middle line:90%
for optimal performance, right?

00:26:18.610 --> 00:26:20.890 align:middle line:84%
Even though we've
evolved to the state,

00:26:20.890 --> 00:26:25.070 align:middle line:84%
we can help it with
science, with technology.

00:26:25.070 --> 00:26:28.360 align:middle line:84%
And so, again, transhumanism
is a huge discipline.

00:26:28.360 --> 00:26:29.860 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to
speak for all of it.

00:26:29.860 --> 00:26:32.950 align:middle line:84%
My main concern with it
is when the technology

00:26:32.950 --> 00:26:35.300 align:middle line:84%
begins to be integrated
into the human body.

00:26:35.300 --> 00:26:36.430 align:middle line:90%
Now, there are, obviously--

00:26:36.430 --> 00:26:37.420 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Can that be good, too?

00:26:37.420 --> 00:26:37.990 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Of course, it can.

00:26:37.990 --> 00:26:39.032 align:middle line:90%
There are great examples.

00:26:39.032 --> 00:26:43.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are
Olympians, the athletes

00:26:43.060 --> 00:26:45.538 align:middle line:84%
who have lost limbs,
for example, Right

00:26:45.538 --> 00:26:46.580 align:middle line:90%
and they're being given--

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:47.622 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Prosthetic legs.

00:26:47.622 --> 00:26:49.180 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: --prosthetic
legs or arms.

00:26:49.180 --> 00:26:52.750 align:middle line:84%
And if you have an
ability to speak,

00:26:52.750 --> 00:26:57.580 align:middle line:84%
it's wonderful to have the
potential for Neuralink.

00:26:57.580 --> 00:26:59.980 align:middle line:84%
My issue, though,
is, ultimately, I

00:26:59.980 --> 00:27:01.900 align:middle line:90%
believe that we are--

00:27:01.900 --> 00:27:04.870 align:middle line:84%
again, we are endowed
by a divine spirit.

00:27:04.870 --> 00:27:07.360 align:middle line:84%
I believe that we have so much
more ability and capability

00:27:07.360 --> 00:27:12.190 align:middle line:84%
within us if we trust
that we are made, really,

00:27:12.190 --> 00:27:16.750 align:middle line:84%
in a beautiful organic and
evolved way with nature.

00:27:16.750 --> 00:27:20.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm worried about taking us
too far away from nature.

00:27:20.450 --> 00:27:22.600 align:middle line:84%
I think we already see
consequences of it.

00:27:22.600 --> 00:27:27.760 align:middle line:84%
Think about how being denatured
for children is affecting,

00:27:27.760 --> 00:27:34.310 align:middle line:84%
let's say, their
minds, their emotions.

00:27:34.310 --> 00:27:38.110 align:middle line:84%
It's like there's a huge issue
with suicide, youth suicide,

00:27:38.110 --> 00:27:38.952 align:middle line:90%
for example.

00:27:38.952 --> 00:27:40.660 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: They just
came out with a report

00:27:40.660 --> 00:27:45.160 align:middle line:84%
that kids, eight and above,
should be treated for anxiety.

00:27:45.160 --> 00:27:46.180 align:middle line:90%
That's crazy.

00:27:46.180 --> 00:27:47.555 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: It's
happening en masse,

00:27:47.555 --> 00:27:50.180 align:middle line:84%
and I believe that we are being
taken too far from nature.

00:27:50.180 --> 00:27:51.638 align:middle line:84%
It's already
happening, as we know,

00:27:51.638 --> 00:27:54.580 align:middle line:84%
with the video games, the amount
of television, and social media

00:27:54.580 --> 00:27:55.622 align:middle line:90%
that we're engaging with.

00:27:55.622 --> 00:27:59.240 align:middle line:84%
But imagine, then, now
putting that into your body.

00:27:59.240 --> 00:28:00.970 align:middle line:84%
We don't understand
the consequences

00:28:00.970 --> 00:28:03.340 align:middle line:90%
of what this will do to us.

00:28:03.340 --> 00:28:07.240 align:middle line:84%
Because we've ultimately evolved
these bodies in conjunction

00:28:07.240 --> 00:28:09.490 align:middle line:90%
with the natural world.

00:28:09.490 --> 00:28:12.530 align:middle line:84%
So I'm very concerned about that
side of the transhuman agenda.

00:28:12.530 --> 00:28:14.110 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
there is an agenda

00:28:14.110 --> 00:28:16.540 align:middle line:90%
to control humanity better.

00:28:16.540 --> 00:28:19.060 align:middle line:84%
Because if, again,
the psychology

00:28:19.060 --> 00:28:21.280 align:middle line:84%
of many of these elite is
that the human being is

00:28:21.280 --> 00:28:25.060 align:middle line:84%
just a biocomputer that,
essentially, the DNA

00:28:25.060 --> 00:28:26.800 align:middle line:84%
is just a bunch of
on/off switches.

00:28:26.800 --> 00:28:29.050 align:middle line:84%
So if we can just figure
out how to manipulate

00:28:29.050 --> 00:28:32.560 align:middle line:84%
the on/off and ones and
zeros like in a computer,

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:35.530 align:middle line:84%
we can create a
more optimal being.

00:28:35.530 --> 00:28:37.720 align:middle line:90%
And I'm very skeptical of that.

00:28:37.720 --> 00:28:39.610 align:middle line:84%
I'm very skeptical of
the consequence of it

00:28:39.610 --> 00:28:42.730 align:middle line:84%
and how much more
harm it will cause.

00:28:42.730 --> 00:28:44.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there
an upside here?

00:28:44.320 --> 00:28:44.830 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Well, of course.

00:28:44.830 --> 00:28:46.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean, their upside,
they claim, of course,

00:28:46.970 --> 00:28:48.260 align:middle line:90%
will be the designer baby.

00:28:48.260 --> 00:28:50.830 align:middle line:84%
We'll get you the baby
that has the freer color.

00:28:50.830 --> 00:28:52.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Free of
this, free of that.

00:28:52.330 --> 00:28:53.920 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: It'll be larger.

00:28:53.920 --> 00:28:56.020 align:middle line:84%
But again, you can't
be free of disease.

00:28:56.020 --> 00:28:57.220 align:middle line:90%
We're in a natural world.

00:28:57.220 --> 00:28:59.230 align:middle line:84%
There's germs, and
bacteria, and viruses.

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:00.520 align:middle line:84%
We've co-evolved with
them for a millenia.

00:29:00.520 --> 00:29:02.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: But they'll
tell you they will.

00:29:02.230 --> 00:29:03.438 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: But that's my point.

00:29:03.438 --> 00:29:04.990 align:middle line:84%
So they say that
there's an upside.

00:29:04.990 --> 00:29:06.880 align:middle line:90%
And again, maybe there is.

00:29:06.880 --> 00:29:10.720 align:middle line:84%
But I believe that the danger
is greater than the upside,

00:29:10.720 --> 00:29:12.560 align:middle line:90%
just like with, again, AI.

00:29:12.560 --> 00:29:14.540 align:middle line:90%
AI has upsides to it.

00:29:14.540 --> 00:29:16.630 align:middle line:84%
But ultimately, who
programs the AI?

00:29:16.630 --> 00:29:19.030 align:middle line:84%
Because if you program
the AI in such a way,

00:29:19.030 --> 00:29:22.730 align:middle line:84%
it can very easily turn
against humanity and say, look,

00:29:22.730 --> 00:29:23.980 align:middle line:90%
we're a stupid species.

00:29:23.980 --> 00:29:25.390 align:middle line:90%
We're irrational.

00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:29.560 align:middle line:84%
For the sake of rationality,
remember, Hitler and others

00:29:29.560 --> 00:29:31.150 align:middle line:90%
created huge genocides.

00:29:31.150 --> 00:29:33.940 align:middle line:84%
If you follow the
logic, it's very easy

00:29:33.940 --> 00:29:35.110 align:middle line:90%
to end up with genocide.

00:29:35.110 --> 00:29:36.400 align:middle line:90%
Because humans are illogical.

00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:38.265 align:middle line:84%
We're irrational, but
that's our beauty.

00:29:38.265 --> 00:29:39.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Our friend
William Henry

00:29:39.640 --> 00:29:43.540 align:middle line:84%
was on "Open Minds,"
talking about the commodity

00:29:43.540 --> 00:29:47.700 align:middle line:84%
texts in relationship to
what you're talking about.

00:29:47.700 --> 00:29:49.770 align:middle line:10%
>>WILLIAM HENRY: Paul
clearly spells out

00:29:49.770 --> 00:29:52.380 align:middle line:10%
this warning in the Book
of Ephisians to say,

00:29:52.380 --> 00:29:55.050 align:middle line:10%
watch out for these
archons and these powers

00:29:55.050 --> 00:29:58.140 align:middle line:10%
that come from other worlds.

00:29:58.140 --> 00:29:59.400 align:middle line:90%
They want our souls.

00:29:59.400 --> 00:30:00.930 align:middle line:90%
And he has a remedy for it.

00:30:00.930 --> 00:30:03.660 align:middle line:10%
He tells us that the way
we can protect ourselves

00:30:03.660 --> 00:30:06.720 align:middle line:10%
is by augmenting
the body, by putting

00:30:06.720 --> 00:30:08.850 align:middle line:10%
on what he calls the
crown of salvation,

00:30:08.850 --> 00:30:10.590 align:middle line:10%
the breastplate
of righteousness,

00:30:10.590 --> 00:30:12.720 align:middle line:10%
the belt of truth,
the sandals of peace,

00:30:12.720 --> 00:30:13.930 align:middle line:10%
and the sword of faith.

00:30:13.930 --> 00:30:15.600 align:middle line:10%
>>MEREDITH: Higher
attributes, virtues.

00:30:15.600 --> 00:30:16.433 align:middle line:10%
>>HENRY: Absolutely.

00:30:16.433 --> 00:30:19.650 align:middle line:10%
Are they or are these
actual physical objects

00:30:19.650 --> 00:30:21.360 align:middle line:10%
he's telling us to go acquire?

00:30:21.360 --> 00:30:23.600 align:middle line:10%
My answer is, they're
psychospiritual attributes.

00:30:23.600 --> 00:30:25.350 align:middle line:10%
>>MEREDITH: They're
psychospiritual, yeah.

00:30:25.350 --> 00:30:27.225 align:middle line:10%
>>HENRY: These are
psychospiritual attributes

00:30:27.225 --> 00:30:28.740 align:middle line:10%
that are developed
from within us,

00:30:28.740 --> 00:30:31.658 align:middle line:10%
that everybody can
activate from within.

00:30:31.658 --> 00:30:33.450 align:middle line:84%
And so, clearly, if
you're looking for them

00:30:33.450 --> 00:30:35.820 align:middle line:84%
as exterior power
tools, it's going

00:30:35.820 --> 00:30:37.110 align:middle line:90%
to take you down one path.

00:30:37.110 --> 00:30:39.012 align:middle line:84%
But if you're looking
at it internally,

00:30:39.012 --> 00:30:40.720 align:middle line:84%
it's going to take
you down another path.

00:30:40.720 --> 00:30:42.803 align:middle line:84%
And clearly, we want to
go down the internal path.

00:30:42.803 --> 00:30:45.060 align:middle line:84%
We don't need this
technology in order

00:30:45.060 --> 00:30:48.600 align:middle line:84%
to be able to do all the
things that our technology is

00:30:48.600 --> 00:30:50.010 align:middle line:90%
making it so easy for us to do.

00:30:50.010 --> 00:30:51.135 align:middle line:90%
>>MEREDITH: Absolutely not.

00:30:51.135 --> 00:30:53.700 align:middle line:84%
And you say that this
heavenly realm written about,

00:30:53.700 --> 00:30:56.100 align:middle line:84%
including the archons, is
also in the Nag Hammadi.

00:30:56.100 --> 00:30:57.360 align:middle line:90%
>>HENRY: Yes, absolutely.

00:30:57.360 --> 00:30:59.850 align:middle line:84%
This is the basis for
all the Gnostic taxes.

00:30:59.850 --> 00:31:02.610 align:middle line:84%
This New Kingdom of
heaven and this new Earth,

00:31:02.610 --> 00:31:06.360 align:middle line:84%
as well as the emergence
of a perfect man, this

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:07.920 align:middle line:90%
is the term they keep using.

00:31:07.920 --> 00:31:10.278 align:middle line:10%
But when you-- as
I have done, have

00:31:10.278 --> 00:31:11.820 align:middle line:10%
gone through these
various traditions

00:31:11.820 --> 00:31:14.760 align:middle line:10%
and tried to understand
what is the perfect human?

00:31:14.760 --> 00:31:17.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, the word perfect
in this context

00:31:17.610 --> 00:31:21.780 align:middle line:84%
means whole, wholly,
and complete.

00:31:21.780 --> 00:31:23.430 align:middle line:84%
So it doesn't mean
that we're going

00:31:23.430 --> 00:31:26.640 align:middle line:84%
to augment ourselves through
some kind of Google technology

00:31:26.640 --> 00:31:27.660 align:middle line:90%
and become perfect.

00:31:27.660 --> 00:31:32.220 align:middle line:84%
Rather, it's a state within
us that everybody can acquire,

00:31:32.220 --> 00:31:34.440 align:middle line:84%
this state of
wholeness and holiness.

00:31:34.440 --> 00:31:36.690 align:middle line:84%
And every spiritual
tradition talks

00:31:36.690 --> 00:31:40.200 align:middle line:84%
about the emergence of a
perfect human being who

00:31:40.200 --> 00:31:42.180 align:middle line:90%
is not a flesh and blood being.

00:31:42.180 --> 00:31:45.000 align:middle line:84%
They all agree
that the human body

00:31:45.000 --> 00:31:47.850 align:middle line:90%
was designed for ascension.

00:31:47.850 --> 00:31:50.760 align:middle line:84%
It was designed to be spun
into a vortex of energy that

00:31:50.760 --> 00:31:53.673 align:middle line:84%
ultimately manifests as
five-colored rainbow light,

00:31:53.673 --> 00:31:54.840 align:middle line:90%
which they call the rainbow.

00:31:54.840 --> 00:31:56.010 align:middle line:84%
>>MEREDITH: When
the time comes, when

00:31:56.010 --> 00:31:58.240 align:middle line:84%
a person reached that point
in their own evolution.

00:31:58.240 --> 00:31:59.040 align:middle line:90%
>>HENRY: Exactly.

00:31:59.040 --> 00:32:02.250 align:middle line:10%
But along the way, there have
been many gurus and avatars

00:32:02.250 --> 00:32:05.610 align:middle line:10%
that have attained the
status to show as the way.

00:32:05.610 --> 00:32:07.350 align:middle line:10%
And something I find
very interesting

00:32:07.350 --> 00:32:11.730 align:middle line:10%
is that when you look into the
Dead Sea Scrolls, for example,

00:32:11.730 --> 00:32:13.950 align:middle line:10%
they were clearly
part of this program

00:32:13.950 --> 00:32:16.890 align:middle line:10%
that was trying to infuse
humanity with a-- call it

00:32:16.890 --> 00:32:19.960 align:middle line:10%
a higher vibrational
being, a new way of living.

00:32:19.960 --> 00:32:23.700 align:middle line:84%
They believed that humans
could transform into angels,

00:32:23.700 --> 00:32:27.330 align:middle line:84%
and that the angels had
come to Earth to show humans

00:32:27.330 --> 00:32:29.910 align:middle line:84%
how to scale the
evolutionary ladder.

00:32:29.910 --> 00:32:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And not through technology,
but psychospiritual means.

00:32:33.360 --> 00:32:36.420 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Let's talk about
technology, for a moment, Sean.

00:32:36.420 --> 00:32:38.850 align:middle line:84%
I remember the days we
used to have pagers,

00:32:38.850 --> 00:32:40.380 align:middle line:90%
probably before you were born.

00:32:40.380 --> 00:32:41.550 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: No, we had pagers.

00:32:41.550 --> 00:32:43.980 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And now, we've
all got smartphones.

00:32:43.980 --> 00:32:45.420 align:middle line:90%
Now, we can go on the internet.

00:32:45.420 --> 00:32:46.770 align:middle line:90%
Now, we can do research.

00:32:46.770 --> 00:32:48.480 align:middle line:90%
Now, you can text people.

00:32:48.480 --> 00:32:51.750 align:middle line:84%
You can send pictures to
friends in Europe instantly.

00:32:51.750 --> 00:32:53.882 align:middle line:90%
What's wrong with that?

00:32:53.882 --> 00:32:55.590 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: I don't have
an issue with that.

00:32:55.590 --> 00:32:57.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm not anti-technology.

00:32:57.930 --> 00:32:59.722 align:middle line:84%
I simply said, don't
put it into your body.

00:32:59.722 --> 00:33:01.513 align:middle line:84%
Be careful about putting
it into your body,

00:33:01.513 --> 00:33:02.580 align:middle line:90%
unless it's, of course--

00:33:02.580 --> 00:33:04.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there are
cases of extreme,

00:33:04.140 --> 00:33:07.150 align:middle line:84%
people that have, again, lost
limbs, have been damaged.

00:33:07.150 --> 00:33:07.950 align:middle line:90%
I understand that.

00:33:07.950 --> 00:33:10.170 align:middle line:84%
But be careful about
putting it into your body.

00:33:10.170 --> 00:33:11.868 align:middle line:84%
Because our cell phone
is emitting EMFs.

00:33:11.868 --> 00:33:13.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I remember
when I was a kid--

00:33:13.410 --> 00:33:14.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's true.

00:33:14.010 --> 00:33:15.030 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: They told
you, don't put the cell

00:33:15.030 --> 00:33:16.590 align:middle line:90%
phone to your head, remember?

00:33:16.590 --> 00:33:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And nowadays, it's like people
have forgotten about that.

00:33:19.680 --> 00:33:21.262 align:middle line:90%
So I'm not against technology.

00:33:21.262 --> 00:33:23.220 align:middle line:84%
And I understand that
humans are going to play.

00:33:23.220 --> 00:33:24.640 align:middle line:84%
I mean, look, this
is what we do.

00:33:24.640 --> 00:33:25.807 align:middle line:90%
This is part of the freedom.

00:33:25.807 --> 00:33:27.870 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not here to tell
people, don't try it.

00:33:27.870 --> 00:33:30.180 align:middle line:84%
Just be mindful of what
you put into your body.

00:33:30.180 --> 00:33:32.070 align:middle line:90%
Be mindful of what you--

00:33:32.070 --> 00:33:34.350 align:middle line:84%
because once you break
that blood-brain barrier,

00:33:34.350 --> 00:33:36.340 align:middle line:84%
once you've embedded
in your body,

00:33:36.340 --> 00:33:38.700 align:middle line:84%
it can be more permanent
or permanent, right?

00:33:38.700 --> 00:33:41.110 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just like
a tattoo, right?

00:33:41.110 --> 00:33:41.940 align:middle line:90%
Be careful.

00:33:41.940 --> 00:33:43.330 align:middle line:90%
Be mindful of what you're doing.

00:33:43.330 --> 00:33:44.580 align:middle line:90%
But we are here to experiment.

00:33:44.580 --> 00:33:45.600 align:middle line:90%
We are here to explore.

00:33:45.600 --> 00:33:51.250 align:middle line:84%
That's an aspect of the
reason why we're here.

00:33:51.250 --> 00:33:52.050 align:middle line:90%
It's to play.

00:33:52.050 --> 00:33:55.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: If you were able to
paint your ideal civilization,

00:33:55.890 --> 00:33:59.040 align:middle line:84%
the vision of the
future, of a human being,

00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:00.272 align:middle line:90%
what would that be?

00:34:00.272 --> 00:34:02.730 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Oh, wow, they would
look like those rainbow beings

00:34:02.730 --> 00:34:03.660 align:middle line:90%
that he was talking about.

00:34:03.660 --> 00:34:04.170 align:middle line:90%
I mean, the sense--

00:34:04.170 --> 00:34:05.520 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: He loves those things.

00:34:05.520 --> 00:34:07.853 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: --the chakra was
activated, filling our energy.

00:34:07.853 --> 00:34:08.730 align:middle line:90%
Look, we're energy.

00:34:08.730 --> 00:34:09.760 align:middle line:90%
We're energy beings.

00:34:09.760 --> 00:34:12.389 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the more we
become attuned to the energy

00:34:12.389 --> 00:34:18.510 align:middle line:84%
that we are, the more that we
can actually, at one level,

00:34:18.510 --> 00:34:21.810 align:middle line:84%
be contained within ourselves
so that we're not always

00:34:21.810 --> 00:34:25.260 align:middle line:84%
looking for external feeding,
going back to our conversation

00:34:25.260 --> 00:34:29.130 align:middle line:84%
earlier, the feeding, the idea
of needing to feed upon others.

00:34:29.130 --> 00:34:29.940 align:middle line:90%
Give me your money.

00:34:29.940 --> 00:34:30.898 align:middle line:90%
Give me your attention.

00:34:30.898 --> 00:34:32.370 align:middle line:90%
Give me your energy.

00:34:32.370 --> 00:34:35.520 align:middle line:84%
If it's reciprocated, this
is the future, I believe.

00:34:35.520 --> 00:34:37.929 align:middle line:84%
The future is
reciprocation of energy.

00:34:37.929 --> 00:34:41.340 align:middle line:84%
As I said, if I buy your
good, I'm an investor.

00:34:41.340 --> 00:34:42.639 align:middle line:90%
We don't think of it that way.

00:34:42.639 --> 00:34:44.790 align:middle line:84%
We think of it as,
I'm a customer.

00:34:44.790 --> 00:34:46.840 align:middle line:84%
What if the future is,
no, I'm an investor.

00:34:46.840 --> 00:34:48.862 align:middle line:84%
So I actually get to
be part of your company

00:34:48.862 --> 00:34:50.070 align:middle line:90%
because I'm investing in you.

00:34:50.070 --> 00:34:52.170 align:middle line:84%
That's the way I want
us to be in the future.

00:34:52.170 --> 00:34:55.170 align:middle line:84%
I want us to be really
attuned to where

00:34:55.170 --> 00:34:56.880 align:middle line:90%
we're putting our energy.

00:34:56.880 --> 00:34:58.350 align:middle line:90%
Because money is energy.

00:34:58.350 --> 00:35:00.863 align:middle line:84%
Who am I choosing
to commerce with?

00:35:00.863 --> 00:35:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Who am I choosing
to commune with?

00:35:02.280 --> 00:35:04.290 align:middle line:84%
Who am I choosing to interact
with and create agreements

00:35:04.290 --> 00:35:05.090 align:middle line:90%
with?

00:35:05.090 --> 00:35:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And as we become more
intentional aware,

00:35:07.110 --> 00:35:09.270 align:middle line:84%
and we realize,
again, our own energy

00:35:09.270 --> 00:35:11.010 align:middle line:84%
and who we share
our energy with,

00:35:11.010 --> 00:35:14.340 align:middle line:84%
then I believe we end up
with a more loving society.

00:35:14.340 --> 00:35:16.200 align:middle line:84%
Because we realize
that our power doesn't

00:35:16.200 --> 00:35:18.570 align:middle line:90%
come from fear but from love.

00:35:18.570 --> 00:35:22.177 align:middle line:84%
Because despite what Machiavelli
said, that if people fear you,

00:35:22.177 --> 00:35:23.010 align:middle line:90%
they won't hurt you.

00:35:23.010 --> 00:35:24.630 align:middle line:84%
Well, go look at
Harvey Weinstein.

00:35:24.630 --> 00:35:25.650 align:middle line:90%
They feared him.

00:35:25.650 --> 00:35:27.330 align:middle line:84%
As soon as he got
weak, what do they do?

00:35:27.330 --> 00:35:29.070 align:middle line:90%
They turned on him.

00:35:29.070 --> 00:35:31.938 align:middle line:84%
There are people that were
previously friends or working

00:35:31.938 --> 00:35:33.480 align:middle line:84%
with him were happy
to throw him out.

00:35:33.480 --> 00:35:34.860 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: They all turned out.

00:35:34.860 --> 00:35:36.480 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: Because that's what
happens if they fear you.

00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:38.313 align:middle line:84%
When they love you,
they're going to show up

00:35:38.313 --> 00:35:39.420 align:middle line:90%
at your sick bed, right?

00:35:39.420 --> 00:35:40.890 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
bring you flowers.

00:35:40.890 --> 00:35:41.490 align:middle line:90%
They're going to--

00:35:41.490 --> 00:35:42.698 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That's human nature.

00:35:42.698 --> 00:35:45.150 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: That's why-- so love
is more powerful than fear.

00:35:45.150 --> 00:35:48.280 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is there a positive
way out for us here?

00:35:48.280 --> 00:35:49.080 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: Of course.

00:35:49.080 --> 00:35:50.250 align:middle line:90%
Of course.

00:35:50.250 --> 00:35:52.560 align:middle line:84%
Look, I'm not here to
predict the earthquakes

00:35:52.560 --> 00:35:55.780 align:middle line:84%
and how many people are going
to be affected or harmed

00:35:55.780 --> 00:35:56.580 align:middle line:90%
in the process.

00:35:56.580 --> 00:35:58.590 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we're here
at this time period

00:35:58.590 --> 00:36:01.590 align:middle line:90%
of massive transformation.

00:36:01.590 --> 00:36:03.720 align:middle line:90%
This is the time of transition.

00:36:03.720 --> 00:36:06.018 align:middle line:84%
But what kind of
humanity prevails?

00:36:06.018 --> 00:36:07.560 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps, there's
going to humanities.

00:36:07.560 --> 00:36:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps, there'll be a
more roboticized humanity

00:36:09.900 --> 00:36:12.810 align:middle line:84%
that will be transhuman,
that will be more, perhaps,

00:36:12.810 --> 00:36:15.990 align:middle line:84%
chipped, that will have
gene editing going in.

00:36:15.990 --> 00:36:19.050 align:middle line:84%
They'll be ready to merge
themselves with their computer

00:36:19.050 --> 00:36:20.740 align:middle line:90%
technology more quickly.

00:36:20.740 --> 00:36:23.850 align:middle line:84%
And then, there'll be those
of us that are more, perhaps,

00:36:23.850 --> 00:36:26.568 align:middle line:84%
organic, more attuned to
our energy and the energy

00:36:26.568 --> 00:36:28.110 align:middle line:84%
that we surround
ourselves with, that

00:36:28.110 --> 00:36:29.235 align:middle line:90%
are more attuned to nature.

00:36:29.235 --> 00:36:33.990 align:middle line:84%
Because nature, Earth is
alive, and she's Gaia.

00:36:33.990 --> 00:36:35.760 align:middle line:90%
She's a big part of the story.

00:36:35.760 --> 00:36:36.960 align:middle line:90%
Because she's waking up.

00:36:36.960 --> 00:36:38.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: She may be the story.

00:36:38.290 --> 00:36:38.820 align:middle line:90%
>>STONE: She is the story.

00:36:38.820 --> 00:36:39.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, she's not the only one.

00:36:39.630 --> 00:36:40.910 align:middle line:84%
Because don't forget,
we got the sun,

00:36:40.910 --> 00:36:42.900 align:middle line:84%
and we've got the solar
system and the cosmos.

00:36:42.900 --> 00:36:45.100 align:middle line:84%
But right now, yeah,
life is happening here.

00:36:45.100 --> 00:36:48.602 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: You should have
added astrologer to your bio.

00:36:48.602 --> 00:36:50.310 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: So this is
where it's at, right?

00:36:50.310 --> 00:36:52.630 align:middle line:84%
This is the playground
of evolution.

00:36:52.630 --> 00:36:55.380 align:middle line:84%
And I think conscious
evolution is taking us

00:36:55.380 --> 00:36:57.870 align:middle line:84%
into a place, where,
who knows, we could

00:36:57.870 --> 00:37:00.490 align:middle line:84%
be getting-- we could get more
telepathic in this coming time

00:37:00.490 --> 00:37:01.290 align:middle line:90%
period.

00:37:01.290 --> 00:37:04.440 align:middle line:84%
We could find all
kinds of abilities

00:37:04.440 --> 00:37:07.920 align:middle line:84%
that would have been considered
mystical or fantastic.

00:37:07.920 --> 00:37:10.930 align:middle line:84%
We don't know where
we're going as a species.

00:37:10.930 --> 00:37:14.820 align:middle line:84%
But I do urge people
be cautious of merging

00:37:14.820 --> 00:37:16.380 align:middle line:90%
the technology with your being.

00:37:16.380 --> 00:37:19.320 align:middle line:84%
Take time with it, but don't
make it your entire life.

00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:21.420 align:middle line:90%
Don't allow it to engross you.

00:37:21.420 --> 00:37:23.350 align:middle line:84%
Because life is
happening all around us.

00:37:23.350 --> 00:37:27.030 align:middle line:84%
It's in, again, the Earth
herself, her activation.

00:37:27.030 --> 00:37:28.650 align:middle line:90%
When we go to touch the tree.

00:37:28.650 --> 00:37:29.820 align:middle line:90%
We touch the ground.

00:37:29.820 --> 00:37:30.900 align:middle line:90%
We walk on the mountain.

00:37:30.900 --> 00:37:31.830 align:middle line:90%
We feel the energy.

00:37:31.830 --> 00:37:34.560 align:middle line:84%
We feel the power of the
sun activating us, right?

00:37:34.560 --> 00:37:37.380 align:middle line:84%
This is where the evolution
is actually occurring.

00:37:37.380 --> 00:37:40.260 align:middle line:84%
It's occurring at those
vibrational levels

00:37:40.260 --> 00:37:41.100 align:middle line:90%
that are invisible.

00:37:41.100 --> 00:37:43.290 align:middle line:84%
It's not just at the level
of what iPhone generation

00:37:43.290 --> 00:37:44.090 align:middle line:90%
you're on.

00:37:44.090 --> 00:37:46.320 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Humankind,
since the ages,

00:37:46.320 --> 00:37:50.760 align:middle line:84%
has expressed itself in the
form of artwork and things

00:37:50.760 --> 00:37:52.250 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:37:52.250 --> 00:37:58.380 align:middle line:84%
Can they depict things in
artwork to change the future?

00:37:58.380 --> 00:38:01.850 align:middle line:84%
>>STONE: So this is a
really interesting question.

00:38:01.850 --> 00:38:03.710 align:middle line:90%
I believe that we are creators.

00:38:03.710 --> 00:38:04.510 align:middle line:90%
And not just me.

00:38:04.510 --> 00:38:05.560 align:middle line:84%
I mean, many people
will say this.

00:38:05.560 --> 00:38:06.700 align:middle line:90%
Humans are creators.

00:38:06.700 --> 00:38:11.890 align:middle line:84%
So why is it so important
that the media plant seeds?

00:38:11.890 --> 00:38:14.508 align:middle line:84%
Because if you are the Earth,
you and I are the Earth,

00:38:14.508 --> 00:38:16.300 align:middle line:84%
we are made of the same
stuff of the Earth.

00:38:16.300 --> 00:38:17.258 align:middle line:90%
What does the Earth do?

00:38:17.258 --> 00:38:19.900 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the seed plants in
the Earth, whe it watered,

00:38:19.900 --> 00:38:20.860 align:middle line:90%
it grows.

00:38:20.860 --> 00:38:23.260 align:middle line:84%
So when seeds are
planted in our mind,

00:38:23.260 --> 00:38:27.720 align:middle line:84%
that grows and that manifests
in our reality, our shared

00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:28.520 align:middle line:90%
reality.

00:38:28.520 --> 00:38:30.730 align:middle line:84%
So the mainstream
media, I believe,

00:38:30.730 --> 00:38:35.750 align:middle line:84%
does plant things that we,
then, collectively manifest.

00:38:35.750 --> 00:38:38.150 align:middle line:84%
As you become more conscious
of what we take in,

00:38:38.150 --> 00:38:41.120 align:middle line:84%
the media we take in, the
stories that we take in,

00:38:41.120 --> 00:38:43.940 align:middle line:84%
I believe we'll be able to
manifest better realities.

00:38:43.940 --> 00:38:46.340 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Interested to get
your reaction to Ben Stewart

