pain and suffering and going

00:39:35.470 --> 00:39:36.673 align:middle line:90%
for pleasure.

00:39:36.673 --> 00:39:38.590 align:middle line:84%
There's something deeply
about the artist that

00:39:38.590 --> 00:39:43.660 align:middle line:84%
takes suffering and pain
and draws forth the beauty

00:39:43.660 --> 00:39:46.870 align:middle line:84%
from within it, and
represents it in a new way,

00:39:46.870 --> 00:39:50.470 align:middle line:84%
and really shows there's
that sovereignty of choice

00:39:50.470 --> 00:39:53.200 align:middle line:84%
and decision making,
which, at present, hasn't

00:39:53.200 --> 00:39:54.460 align:middle line:90%
been eradicated.

00:39:54.460 --> 00:39:57.850 align:middle line:84%
So we're talking about
linking our minds to computer

00:39:57.850 --> 00:39:59.170 align:middle line:90%
and cloud-based technology.

00:39:59.170 --> 00:40:01.990 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, that can
become the singular mind.

00:40:01.990 --> 00:40:04.030 align:middle line:84%
This is the whole
post-human idea.

00:40:04.030 --> 00:40:05.860 align:middle line:90%
It's after transhumanism.

00:40:05.860 --> 00:40:07.540 align:middle line:90%
It's having that singular mind.

00:40:07.540 --> 00:40:09.405 align:middle line:90%
And where does the artist go?

00:40:09.405 --> 00:40:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And there's a lot of people
